headline: Wells Fargo Stays Overweight on Dollar Tree, Keeps $105 Target
summary: Wells Fargo has reaffirmed its Overweight rating on Dollar Tree (NASDAQ: DLTR), sticking with a $105 price target in early June. The stock, now at $99.05, has been volatile, with analyst targets ranging widely between $70 and $109. The firm wasn’t surprised by the recent dip following Dollar Tree’s Q1 results.
